I'd add in a few cents of my own;

{{champion:157}} + Hard CC support or a knock up support. Ideally, ones like {{champion:12}} or {{champion:53}} .

Played it a few times, personal experience is that it works pretty well. Late game will have issues if you don't have someone to knock up enemies for you, though.

And an oddball: {{champion:150}} 

Originally in PBE, he was picked as an ADC quite a bit of the time, and it's pretty obvious to see why. His Q scaled off a lot of AD and had range, his W was pretty much vayne's W but with movement speed and magic damage, and his E not only allowed for engage/escape but also gave attack speed. The reason it may not always work is due to his mega form, which if you don't get a good initiation off of, will struggle to really assist in a fight.

I'd honestly consider doing Gnar bot lane quite a bit more often if it weren't for the fact that I'm kind of terrible at marksmen and the general stigma that would happen if I tried to pick him for bot lane.
